<h1>Clump</h1>

<p>
This tool recategorizes data in a raster image by grouping cells that form physically discrete, connected areas into unique categories. Essentially this will produce a patch map from an input categorical image. The input image should either be Boolean (1's and 0's) or categorical. The input image could be created using the <b><i>Reclass</i></b> tool or one of the comparison operators (<b><i>GreaterThan</i></b>, <b><i>LessThan</i></b>, <b><i>GreaterThanEqualTo</i></b>, <b><i>LessThanEqualTo</i></b>, <b><i>EqualTo</i></b>, <b><i>NotEqualTo</i></b>). Check the 'Treat zeros as background cells' checkbox if you would like to only assigned contiguous groups of non-zero values in the input image unique identifiers.</p>


